<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870914-0001 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:United Artists Communications Inc.</HL><DD> 09/14/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UACIBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   UNITED ARTISTS COMMUNICATIONS INC. said it is offering $100 million of subordinated debentures due Sept. 15, 2002, priced at par to yield 6.375%. Interest on the debentures is payable March 15 and Sept. 15, starting March 15, 1988. They are convertible at any time before maturity into United common stock at an initial conversion price of $35.75 a share. In national over-the-counter trading Friday, the stock closed at $27.25, down 50 cents. The Englewood, Colo., cable television and movie theater concern said it will use the proceeds to pay bank debt. Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. is the underwriter. </TEXT></DOC>